.TH ZPEN 1 "May 2026" "zpen 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
zpen \- fullscreen transparent drawing overlay for X11
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B zpen
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B zpen
creates a transparent fullscreen layer over the desktop that lets you
annotate, sketch, and highlight anything on screen. It is intended for
presentations, tutorials, code reviews, and quick visual communication.
.PP
The overlay grabs keyboard focus on launch. Drawings are non-destructive
and exist only in the overlay window; press
.B Esc
to dismiss it. zpen targets X11 desktops with a compositor for transparency;
on Wayland it works through XWayland.
.PP
zpen requires the
.BR xclip (1)
helper for clipboard operations and
optionally
.BR tesseract (1)
for OCR.
.SH KEY BINDINGS
.SS Drawing tools
.TP
.B p
Pen \(em freehand drawing with smoothing.
.TP
.B l
Straight line.
.TP
.B a
Arrow. Hold
.B Shift
while drawing for a freehand path with an auto-oriented arrowhead.
.TP
.B r
Rectangle. Press again to toggle rounded corners.
.TP
.B c
Circle.
.TP
.B {
Curly brace; direction is auto-detected (opening vs closing).
.TP
.B [
Square bracket; direction is auto-detected.
.TP
.B b
Blur brush.
.TP
.B t
Text input. Type characters, press
.B Esc
to commit and exit text mode.
.TP
.B n
Numbered step marker (auto-incrementing).
.SS Style modifiers
.TP
.B Space \fRor\fB Right
Next colour.
.TP
.B Left
Previous colour.
.TP
.B +\fR / \fB-
Increase / decrease pen thickness.
.TP
.B 0
Reset pen thickness to default.
.TP
.B *
Toggle solid / dashed line style.
.TP
.B Shift\fR + draw on rectangle/circle
Translucent (~20%) fill of the active colour.
.SS Screenshots and clipboard
.TP
.B f
Select a region and save it to a PNG under
.IR ~/.zpen/ .
.TP
.B s
Select a region, copy it to the clipboard, and exit.
.TP
.B o
Select a region, run OCR on it, and copy the recognised text to the
clipboard. Requires
.BR tesseract (1).
.TP
.B Ctrl+C
Select a region and copy to clipboard without exiting.
.TP
.B Ctrl+V
Paste a clipboard image at the mouse cursor.
.SS Edit history
.TP
.B u\fR or \fBCtrl+Z
Undo (up to 20 steps).
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+Z\fR or \fBCtrl+Shift+Y
Redo.
.SS Exit
.TP
.B Esc
Quit zpen.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.zpen/
Created on first screenshot, mode 0700. Saved screenshots are written here
as
.IR imgYYYYMMDDHHMMSS.png .
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
If set and writable, used for short-lived temp files
created during clipboard paste and OCR. Falls back to
.IR /tmp .
.TP
.B HOME
Used to locate
.IR ~/.zpen/ .
If unset, the location is read from
.BR getpwuid (3).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR xclip (1),
.BR tesseract (1)
